=== Turn example (Assuming 2 actions)

Priest : Stress: Affinity for fire (pray)
Cleric : Stress: (Convoque affinity) - Fire - Blinding light attack (1d6)
Priest : Stress: Affinity Rally on paladin (dice size = d12)
Paladin : Attack (2d12)
Paladin : Attack (2d12)
Cleric : Attack (1d6) 
 

== Balanced Party

=== Fighter
- Tradition: Fateful
  - Specialties
    - Opportunist fighting
      - [ ] Passive +1 Dice on *Open* Enemies 
      - [ ] Reliable test (2): Strength tests
      - [ ] Stress Action: Feint / Topple : roll attack + inflict *Open*
    - Trapper
      - [ ] Passive: Attack against trap ennemies are d12 
    - Ice elemental magic
      - [ ] Ice Rituals

=== Healer
- Tradition: Supported
  - Specialties
    - Herborist
      - [x] Passive: When removing a threat, you also remove one stress
    - Water magic
      - [ ] Convoque affinity: Water - Your vessel performs the following actions: Heal (heal for 1d, removes one *blight* or *dread* from a character)
      - [ ] Convoque affinity: Water - Your vessel performs the following actions: drown (Inflict *Water* and creates a dice pool of 1d for each *Water* on target)
      - [ ] Water Rituals
    - Ice magic
      - [ ] Convoque affinity: Trapped inder ice - Your vessel performs the following actions: attack + add *trap* to *Water* 

=== Face
- Tradition: knowledgeable
  - Specialties
    - Socialite
      - [ ] Draw knowledge when you gossip
      - [ ] Reliable test (2) : Influence and persuasion
      - [ ] Apply Knowledge (Cups / Hearts) : Reliable test (4) : Influence using Emotions, apply *fool*
    - Herald
      - [ ] Affinity for 2 threat (Trap and Dread)
      - [ ] Affinity rally (Convoque Affinity) 

=== Turn example (Assuming 2 actions)

Healer : Stress : Convoque Affinity - Water - Drown (1d6 + *Water*)
Healer : Stress : Trapped inder ice - (1d6 + *trap*)
Fighter : Stress: Feign / Topple (d12)
Fighter : Attack (2d12)
Face : Apply knowledge : change value of d12 to [Card]
Face : Apply knowledge : Influence using emotions: Surrender [Card]
 
 
